      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>1,3-Pentadiene is much more reactive in Diels–Alder reactions than 2,4-pentadienal. Why might this be?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdlFVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--7f51373ae7d71fb2d63646a58516c7d5d9557121/OChem_14_EC_020.jpg\" alt=\"1,3-pentadiene has a 5-carbon chain with doiuble bonds between C1-C2 and C3-C4. 2,4-Pentadienal has a 5-carbon chain with doiuble bonds between C2-C3 and C4-C5 and a carbonyl group at C1\">",
